@startuml
title Atlas Conventions - Relation Grammar and Status Tags
left to right direction
hide empty members

class "Relation Verb Set" as VerbSet {
  +defines
  +constrains
  +drives
  +depends_on
  +realizes
  +materializes
  +emits
  +validates
  +freezes
  +commits
}

class "Confidence Tag" as Confidence {
  +high
  +medium
  +low
  +uncertain
}

class "Diagram Node" as NodeA
class "Diagram Node" as NodeB
class "Edge Label Rule" as Rule {
  +format = "verb + payload + directional preposition"
  +example = "emits typed intents via Capability Runtime Domain"
  +ban = "unlabeled or destination-implicit structural edges"
}

class "Decision Contract Rule" as DecisionRule {
  +source = "50_decision_contracts.puml"
  +status = "normative for scripting atlas"
}

NodeA -[#1E88E5]-> NodeB : defines contract boundary for NodeB [high]
VerbSet -[#1E88E5]-> Rule : constrains edge vocabulary within authoring rules
Confidence -[#1E88E5]-> Rule : annotates certainty level within edge labels
Rule -[#1E88E5]-> NodeA : constrains authoring style within diagram nodes
DecisionRule -[#1E88E5]-> Rule : constrains relation semantics across atlas

legend right
  Conventions:
  - Label structural edges with explicit verbs.
  - Prefer "verb + payload + destination context" edge text.
  - Include a directional preposition (`to`, `in`, `via`, `within`, `across`) where meaningful.
  - <color:#1E88E5>Blue</color> = constraints / definition authority.
  - <color:#43A047>Green</color> = data and intent flow in runtime state.
  - <color:#FB8C00>Orange</color> = control/orchestration progression.
  - <color:#8E24AA>Purple</color> = feedback/return flow back to caller context.
  - <color:#E53935>Red</color> = failure or panic path.
  - <color:#00897B>Teal</color> = structure projection/materialization links.
  - Add confidence in brackets when uncertain.
  - Use stereotypes only for design certainty, not for type category.
  - Keep sequence/activity labels action-oriented.
  - Decision contracts in `50_decision_contracts.puml` are normative.
endlegend
@enduml
